INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3000','letter','1776-10-24','Fort Lee','NJ','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','Inclosed you have a copy of the letter, in answer to mine to Congress, relative to cartridges. As soon as the cartridges come up, they shall be forwarded.','ltr_nag3000.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3001','letter','1776-10-31','Fort Lee','NJ','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','The enemy have possession of Fort Independence, on the heights above King\'s Bridge. They made their appearance the night before last. We had got every thing of value away.','ltr_nag3001.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3002','letter','1776-10-07','Fort Lee','NJ','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','I find the enemy are encamped right opposite, to the number of between three and four thousand ; and the Major adds, from their disposition and search after boats, they design to cross the river.','ltr_nag3002.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3003','letter','1776-10-09','Fort Lee','NJ','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','The stores at Dobbs\'s Ferry I had just given orders to the Quartermaster to prepare wagons to remove. I think the enemy will meet with some difficulty in crossing the river at Dobbs\'s Ferry. However, it is not best to trust too much to the expected difficulties they may meet there.','ltr_nag3003.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3004','letter','1776-05-21','Long Island','NY','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','As I have no desire of quitting the service, I hope the Congress will take no measure that will lay me under the disagreeable necessity of doing it.','ltr_nag3004.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3005','letter','1776-07-25','Long Island','NY','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','The science or art of war requires a freedom of thought, and leisure to reflect upon the various incidents that daily occur, which cannot be had where the whole of one\'s time is engrossed in clerical employments.','ltr_nag3005.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3200','letter','1778-07-21','Camp At The Plains','','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','Your Excellency has made me very unhappy. I can submit very patiently to deserved censure ; but it wounds my feelings exceedingly to meet with a rebuke for doing what I conceived to be a proper part of my duty, and in the order of things.','ltr_nag3200.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume II., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3201','letter','1778-08-28','Newport','RI','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','In my last I communicated to your Excellency the departure of the Count D Estaing with his fleet, for Boston. This disagreeable event has, as I apprehend, ruined all our operations.','ltr_nag3201.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume II., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3202','letter','1778-09-16','Boston','MA','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','The growing extravagance of the people, and the increasing demand for the article of forage in this quarter, have become a very alarming affair. Hay is from sixty to eighty dollars a ton, and upon the rise.','ltr_nag3202.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume II., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3203','letter','1779-04-24','Philadelphia','PA','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','I am happy to find you have wrote so fully to Congress, upon the disagreeable consequences that may follow from starving the Quarter master\'s department at this critical season.','ltr_nag3203.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume II., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3204','letter','1779-04-26','Philadelphia','PA','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','Most certain, my inclination leads me to a resignation. My reputation I value more than any advantages of gain ; and I consider it in great danger.','ltr_nag3204.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume II., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3205','letter','1779-11-14','West Point','NY','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','Your Excellency undoubtedly has frequently had under consideration a proper position for winter-quarters. It is not always in the power of a General to take a position most favorable to his wishes','ltr_nag3205.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume II., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3206','letter','1780-01-00','Morristown','NJ','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','I have repeatedly mentioned to your Excellency, for some months past, that the supplies of money furnished the department were very unequal to the current expenses.','ltr_nag3206.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume II., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3207','letter','1780-02-07','Morristown','NJ','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','The inclosed copy of a representation from Colonel Barry, an Assistant Deputy-Quartermaster-General in this State, will show your Excellency that a new difficulty has arisen to delay transportation.','ltr_nag3207.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume II., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3208','letter','1780-03-06','Morristown','NJ','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','Inclosed I send your Excellency a copy of my last letter to Congress, to which they have given no answer, and which necessarily involves very important consequences.','ltr_nag3208.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume II., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3209','letter','1780-03-31','Philadelphia','PA','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','Many people are apprehensive for the fall of Charleston ; and I think it in jeopardy, as well as the troops under Lincoln\'s command. I am more anxious for the fate of the troops than the city.','ltr_nag3209.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume II., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3210','letter','1780-04-02','Philadelphia','PA','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','There would be no difficulty, either in the one case or the other, could the treasury furnish the proper supplies of cash. But in its present exhausted state, with the enormous demands upon the department, the agents have neither credit nor influence equal to the business.','ltr_nag3210.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume II., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3211','letter','1780-05-23','Morristown','NJ','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','I have had a long conversation with General Schuyler this morning, and have seen the powers and appointments upon the present business intrusted to the direction of the Committee, as well as their powers to act under.','ltr_nag3211.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume II., Jared Sparks, 1853');
